us_yields <- read_csv("clean_data/us_crop_data.csv")
## Rows: 522 Columns: 3
##  Column specification 
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (1): commodity
## dbl (2): year, tonnes_per_ha
## 
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
ggplot(wi_yields)+
  geom_line(aes(year, tonnes_per_ha, color=commodity))+
  labs(x="Year", y="Tonnes Per Hectacre", color="Commodity")

ggplot(us_yields)+
  geom_line(aes(year, tonnes_per_ha, color=commodity))+
  labs(x="Year", y="Tonnes Per Hectacre", color="Commodity")

us_yields |> filter(commodity=="barley"|commodity=="corn"|commodity=="soybeans"|commodity=="wheat") |> 
  bind_rows(wi_yields, .id="level") |> 
  mutate(level = case_when(level==1 ~ "US",
                           TRUE ~ "Wisconsin")) |> 
  filter(year>1960) |> 
  ggplot()+
    geom_line(aes(year, tonnes_per_ha, color=commodity))+
    facet_grid(level~.) +
    labs(x="Year", y="Tonnes Per Hectacre", color="Commodity")

wi_weather <- read_csv("clean_data/monthly_wi_weather.csv")
## Rows: 1548 Columns: 5
##  Column specification 
## Delimiter: ","
## dbl  (4): precipitation, avg_temp, max_temp, min_temp
## date (1): date
## 
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
wi_weather
## # A tibble: 1,548  5
##    date       precipitation avg_temp max_temp min_temp
##    <date>             <dbl>    <dbl>    <dbl>    <dbl>

##  2 1895-02-01          0.52      8.9     20.7     -2.8
##  3 1895-03-01          0.47     25.7     37.3     14.1
##  4 1895-04-01          1.21     46.3     59       33.7
##  5 1895-05-01          4.33     56.2     69.4     43  
##  6 1895-06-01          3.08     66.2     79.2     53.3
##  7 1895-07-01          2.79     66.7     80.6     52.7
##  8 1895-08-01          2.48     67.2     80.5     54  
##  9 1895-09-01          3.48     62       74       49.9
## 10 1895-10-01          0.52     39.8     51.9     27.7
## #  1,538 more rows
wi_weather |> 
  group_by(year = year(date)) |> 
  summarize(max_temp=max(max_temp), avg_temp=mean(avg_temp), min_temp=min(min_temp)) |> 
  pivot_longer(cols=-year, names_to="Temperature") |> 
  ggplot(aes(year, value))+
  geom_line(aes(color=Temperature))+
  labs(title="Wisconsin Temperatures", x="Year", y="Temp in F")+
  scale_color_manual(labels = c("Average", "Max", "Min"),
                     values = c("green", "red", "blue"))

p1<-ggplot(wi_yields)+
  geom_line(aes(year, tonnes_per_ha, color=commodity))+
  labs(x="", y="Tonnes Per Hectacre", color="Commodity")
p2<-wi_weather |> 
  group_by(year = year(date)) |> 
  summarize(precipitation=sum(precipitation)) |> 
  filter(year>1923) |> 
  ggplot()+
  geom_line(aes(year, precipitation))+
  labs(x="Year", y="Precipitation (inches)")
p1/p2+
  plot_annotation("Wisconsin Annual Crop Yields vs Annual Precipitation")
